question:
District category contains Entertainment District, Historic Downtown, and Warehouse District.
Supermarkets category contains Lulu Hypermarket, Boxed, and Earth Fare.
Product category contains Pretzels, Canned Vegetables, and Ice Cream.
The number of each Earth Fare 's Canned Vegetables equals the difference of each Warehouse District 's Supermarkets and each Entertainment District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Entertainment District 's Boxed equals 11.
The number of each Warehouse District 's Earth Fare equals 20 more than each Warehouse District 's Boxed.
The number of each Historic Downtown 's Boxed equals 19.
The number of each Warehouse District 's Boxed equals 2 more than the sum of each Entertainment District 's Supermarkets and each Entertainment District 's Boxed.
The number of each Historic Downtown 's Earth Fare equals each Warehouse District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Lulu Hypermarket 's Canned Vegetables equals 3.
The number of each Boxed 's Ice Cream equals 4 more than each Warehouse District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Boxed 's Pretzels equals each Warehouse District 's Earth Fare.
How many Earth Fare does Historic Downtown have?
solution:
Define each Entertainment District 's Boxed as p; So p = 11.
Define each Entertainment District 's Supermarkets as L; So L = p = 11.
Define each Warehouse District 's Boxed as q; r = L + p = 11 + 11 = 22; So q = 2 + r = 2 + 22 = 1.
Define each Warehouse District 's Earth Fare as G; So G = 20 + q = 20 + 1 = 21.
Define each Warehouse District 's Supermarkets as u; So u = q + G = 1 + 21 = 22.
Define each Historic Downtown 's Earth Fare as P; So P = u = 22.
